    <question>
        <prompt>Robert La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign emphasized:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Conservative economic policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Opposition to corporate power and monopolies</option>
            <option letter="c">Support for big business</option>
            <option letter="d">Restriction of labor rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign emphasized opposition to corporate power and monopolies, advocating for public ownership of natural resources, stronger labor rights, and farm relief. His platform represented a direct challenge to the conservative Republican policies of the 1920s, though his defeat demonstrated the declining influence of progressivism during this period.</explanation>
    </question>
